HOUSE BILL 1102
P6 6lr3020
CF SB 748
By: Delegates Buckel, Hinebaugh, and Baker
Introduced and read first time: February 11, 2026
Assigned to: Appropriations
Committee Report: Favorable
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 8, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Correctional Officers’ Retirement System – Allegany County
3 FOR the purpose of requiring membership in the Correctional Officers’ Retirement System
4 for certain local detention center officers of Allegany County in the event Allegany
5 County becomes a participating governmental unit in the Correctional Officers’
6 Retirement System; providing that certain local detention center officers who join
7 the Correctional Officers’ Retirement System and receive certain service credit shall
8 no longer be members of the Employees’ Pension System; and generally relating to
9 Allegany County’s participation in the Correctional Officers’ Retirement System.
10 BY adding to
11 Article – State Personnel and Pensions
12 Section 31–2B–09
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – State Personnel and Pensions
18 31–2B–09.
19 (A) THIS SECTION APPLIES TO AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS A LOCAL DETENTION
20 CENTER OFFICER OF ALLEGANY COUNTY BEFORE THE EFFECTIVE DATE AND WHO
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb1102*

2 HOUSE BILL 1102
1 REMAINS A LOCAL DETENTION CENTER OFFICER OF ALLEGANY COUNTY THROUGH
2 THE EFFECTIVE DATE.
3 (B) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW, IF ALLEGANY
4 COUNTY BECOMES A PARTICIPATING GOVERNMENTAL UNIT IN THE CORRECTIONAL
5 OFFICERS’ RETIREMENT SYSTEM, MEMBERSHIP IN THE CORRECTIONAL OFFICERS’
6 RETIREMENT SYSTEM IS MANDATORY FOR AN INDIVIDUAL DESCRIBED UNDER
7 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION.
8 (C) IF ALLEGANY COUNTY COMMENCES PARTICIPATION IN THE
9 CORRECTIONAL OFFICERS’ RETIREMENT SYSTEM IN ACCORDANCE WITH
10 SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION, AN INDIVIDUAL DESCRIBED UNDER SUBSECTION
11 (A) OF THIS SECTION IS ENTITLED TO ELIGIBILITY SERVICE AND CREDITABLE
12 SERVICE IN THE CORRECTIONAL OFFICERS’ RETIREMENT SYSTEM FOR
13 EMPLOYMENT WITH ALLEGANY COUNTY BEFORE THE EFFECTIVE DATE.
14 (D) ON JOINING THE CORRECTIONAL OFFICERS’ RETIREMENT SYSTEM
15 AND RECEIVING SERVICE CREDIT AS PROVIDED UNDER SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS
16 SECTION, AN INDIVIDUAL DESCRIBED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION
17 SHALL:
18 (1) NO LONGER BE A MEMBER OF THE EMPLOYEES’ PENSION
19 SYSTEM; AND
20 (2) HAVE NO FURTHER RIGHTS TO ANY BENEFIT IN THE EMPLOYEES’
21 PENSION SYSTEM.
22 (E) THE TRANSFER OF CREDITABLE SERVICE FOR AN INDIVIDUAL
23 DESCRIBED IN SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION WHO IS A MEMBER OF THE
24 EMPLOYEES’ PENSION SYSTEM THROUGH THE EFFECTIVE DATE, AND WHO
25 TRANSFERS TO THE CORRECTIONAL OFFICERS’ RETIREMENT SYSTEM UNDER THIS
26 SECTION, IS NOT GOVERNED BY TITLE 37 OF THIS ARTICLE.
27 (F) IF ALLEGANY COUNTY BECOMES A PARTICIPATING GOVERNMENTAL
28 UNIT IN THE CORRECTIONAL OFFICERS’ RETIREMENT SYSTEM, § 31–2B–05(C) OF
29 THIS SUBTITLE SHALL GOVERN THE TRANSFER AND CREDITING OF ASSETS ON THE
30 EFFECTIVE DATE.
31 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
32 1, 2026.

